==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Availability
<hw>A*vail`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Availabilities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being available;
availableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The word is sometimes used derogatively in the sense of
⟦ldquo⟧mere availableness,⟦rdquo⟧ or capability of success without
regard to worthiness.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was . . . nominated for his <qex>availability</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is available.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Available</ent>⟦br⟧
